{{Religious text primary|date=October 2011}}
According to the [[Book of Mormon]], '''Gideon''' was a faithful [[Nephite]] leader, a strong man, and an enemy to King Noah.<ref>Mosiah 19: 4-8</ref> After King Noah's expulsion and death by fire, Gideon counseled with Noah's son, King Limhi.<ref>Mosiah 20:17-22</ref>  He proposed a plan for escaping from [[Lamanite]] bondage.<ref>Mosiah 22: 3-9</ref> Gideon grew to be an old man, and was killed by [[Nehor]].<ref>Alma 1:8-10</ref> After his death, a city of the Nephites was named after him.

