'''Nang''', is a term used by [[Nihang]] [[Sikh]]s for a member guilty of religious misconduct. In that context, nang can mean either ''kangāl'' ({{lang-pa|ਕੰਗਾਲ}} "destitute") or ''nanga'' (one without clothes).<ref name="nangmahan">Nang, Mahankosh</ref> If a member of Nihang army is convicted via [[court-martial]], his royal blue uniform is removed and his license of to keep arms is cancelled, leading to his excommunication from the [[Khalsa]]. Only [[Jathedar]]s of Nihang Dals such as Budha Dal have authority to punish their army members after trial.

