{{Unreferenced|date=July 2011}}
'''Nauruan indigenous religion''' is a [[monotheism|monotheistic]] system of belief that includes a [[Goddess|female deity]] called [[Eijebong]] and an island of spirits called [[Buitani]]. Believers say that the sky and the earth were created by a [[spider]] called [[Areop-Enap]]. There are very few, if any, people on the island who still subscribe to this religion, because of the dominant belief of [[Christianity]] imposed upon them by Christian colonization.

