{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Psilocybe liniformans'' var. ''americana''}} {{Infraspeciesbox | image = | genus = Psilocybe | species = liniformans | varietas = americana | authority = Guzmán & Stamets | synonyms = | range_map = | range_map_caption = }} {{mycomorphbox | name = Psilocybe liniformans var. americana | whichGills = adnexed | whichGills2 = | capShape = convex | capShape2 = | hymeniumType=gills | stipeCharacter=bare | ecologicalType=saprotrophic | sporePrintColor=purple-brown | howEdible=psychoactive }}
'''''Psilocybe liniformans'' var. ''americana''''', is a [[psilocybin mushroom]] in the family [[Hymenogastraceae]]. It is in the section Semilanceatae of ''[[Psilocybe]]'' and has [[psilocybin]] as its main active compound.
==Description== *The '''cap''' is 1 — 2.5&nbsp;cm [[wikt:convex|convex]] to nearly plane, and is sometimes broadly [[wikt:umbonate|umbonate]] but not [[wikt:papillate|papillate]]. It is smooth, dull grayish brown to slightly [[wikt:olivacous|olivacous]], more reddish at the center, [[hygrophanous]], and becoming straw brown when dry with the center remaining more brownish. It sometimes has a bluish green tone, or olivacous tones at the margin when young. *The '''gills''' are [[adnexed]], [[subdistant]], broad, and dark chocolate brown to purplish brown with age. *The '''spores''' are dark purple brown, [[ellipsoid]], and 13 — 14.5 by 7.5 — 8.8(10)[[µm]]. *The '''stipe''' is 1.4 — 3.0&nbsp;cm by 1 – 2&nbsp;mm, equal, enlarging at the base. It is whitish to very pale brownish, darker below, bruising blue, and finely fibrillose in the lower portion. The partial veil is thin and soon disappears. *The '''taste''' is weak to somewhat [[farinaceous]]; The '''odor''' is strongly aromatic to [[farinaceous]]. *'''Microscopic features''': The [[basidium|basidia]] are 4-spored and [[pleurocystidium|pleurocystidia]] are absent. The [[cheilocystidia]] are 22 — 33 by 5.5 — 9 [[µm]], [[wikt:lageniform|lageniform]] and have an extended neck.
==Habitat and formation== ''Psilocybe liniformans'' var. ''americana'' is found scattered to [[wikt:gregarious|gregarious]] in rich pastures or grasslands, fruiting from summer to early winter. It has been collected in [[Washington (U.S. state)|Washington]], [[Oregon]], and [[Michigan]], and has also been reported from [[Chile]] where it fruits in the spring. This mushroom is very close to the type variety; the main difference is the lack of a gelatinous layer on the edge of the [[lamella (mycology)|lamella]]e and the [[wikt:terricolous|terricolous]] habitat.
