'''Sharaf al-Muluk''' ([[Persian language|Persian]]: شرف الملوک) was the ruler of the [[Bavand dynasty]] from 1328 to 1334. He was the son and successor of [[Shah-Kaykhusraw]]. Nothing is known about Sharaf; he died in 1334, and was succeeded by his brother [[Hasan II of Tabaristan]].

